Exactly.  A struct of function pointers would be fine too.  Example:

```
struct otDelegate_s 
{
    void (*onBeaconScanResult)(void *context,
                                  const otMacBeaconData *beacon);
    void (*onScanDone)(void *context, int status);
    // ...
} otDelegate_t;

void otSetDelegate(const struct otDelegate_t *new_delegate, void *context);
```
